  "text": "Case Material Titanium Case size 47mm Colors Titanium Silver; Titanium Gray; Titanium White Display 1.5\" AMOLED CPU Samsung Exynos W1000 A pricey smartwatch that packs all the best features. Get it now for half off while you still can, as Best Buy drops the price to just $325. If you don't mind a large watch and want Samsung's most premium wearable, the Galaxy Watch Ultra is the way to go. You're getting solid build quality, excellent features, and a price that now comes in at just half of its original retail. For a limited time, you can score the Galaxy Watch Ultra for 50% off, coming in at just $325. This is the best price we've seen on this watch, and it's only available today, so get it while you still can. Related What's great about the Galaxy Watch Ultra? The Galaxy Watch Ultra comes in just one size at 47mm and features a large and beautiful 1.5-inch AMOLED display that reaches an impressive brightness of 3,000 nits. You also get premium materials on the case with titanium, and the display is protected using sapphire. The combination of these materials means you get a light yet durable smartwatch, which is perfect if you're looking to take this device outside your typical everyday settings. In addition to the touchscreen, you also get physical buttons for navigation, along with a hotkey that pops on your favorite workout mode with just the push of a button. The watch is powered by Wear OS, which means you'll get frequent updates that improve the overall experience, along with access to the best apps available. The watch can track health and fitness metrics without breaking a sweat, and also delivers data about sleep quality and stress levels. The battery life is pretty good too, coming in at around two days with normal use. Although there is a new model of this watch launching soon, the only difference is that you're getting more storage with the new watch, which makes this model a far better value at just $325. Be sure to get it now though, because this sale is only going to be around for one more day.",
